<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[860,964,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="46">gladiatus</emphasis>
(gladiate), referring to the sword-shaped juxta of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
